-- Ukraine Coal Mine Blast Kills One Worker, Nine Hospitalized
-- B y   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 2012-02-07T07:55:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-07/ukraine-coal-mine-blast-kills-one-worker-nine-hospitalized.html
One coal miner was killed and nine
were hospitalized after an explosion at Pivnichna mine near
Dzerzhynsk city in eastern Ukraine, the Emergency Situations
Ministry said.  The blast occurred at 10:56 p.m. Kiev time yesterday, the
ministry, based in capital Kiev, said in a  statement  on its
website. The mine, operated by state company Dzerzhynskvuhillya,
is closed as the ministry investigates what caused the blast,
according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Daryna Krasnolutska in Kiev at 
